//  COMPCHK2, each group must be assigned a unique Group ID (in
//  looking at this MIF, you will note that it has been constructed
//  to include a unique ID for each group).	When using these
//  groups to construct your own MIF, you are NOT required to use
//  the group IDs presented here.  You ARE required, however, to
//  retain the group's class string, since it is the class string
//  which uniquely identifies each group.
